aVBut it never really occurred to me
p88
aVthat my love of cars and trucks
p89
aVwould ever be in conflict with nature.
p90
aVAnd that was true
p91
aVuntil I got to college.
p92
aVAnd when I got to college, you can imagine my surprise
p93
aVwhen I would go to class
p94
aVand a number of my professors would say
p95
aVthat Ford Motor Company and my family
p96
aVwas everything that was wrong with our country.
p97
aVThey thought that we were more interested, as an industry,
p98
aVin profits, rather than progress,
